<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-12-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-12-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="194" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Snyder</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-12-26"><hi rend="italic">December 26,
                                    1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Snyder reports that the Chapinero line, Bogotá City Railway Company,
                            an American corporation of New York City, was forcibly seized by the
                            authorities of the Department of Cundinamarca on Christmas. Papers will
                            be sent by next mail. Awaiting instructions.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>